$interpreted: Soldier: Sharice? Aren't you on vacation? You're driving this chariot for...
Sharice: Uh...since I rarely get off, I figured I'd travel a bit. This is just my luggage.
Soldier: Isn't that a little bit too much? You need a chariot to fit it all...
Soldier: General Lucien, what are you doing here?
Fredrica: Just accompanying her. Making sure nothing happens to this vital young woman while she is away~
Soldier: Something happens? What would happen?
Fredrica: Aye ya! We're good. I'll just stop here. Leave everything else up to me. You all just have a fun vacation~
Sharice: There's no one here. Everyone can come out.
Naya: *sigh*~ Give it up for Fredrica, getting past the guards so smoothly!
Sione: Never thought Fredrica wouldn't want to go just because there won't be any men there. If I knew it'd be that easy, I wouldn't have had to do anything.
Angelia: Is...is it really okay for me to sneak out like this?
Naya: Angel, why are you furrowing your brows like that? We're already out. Don't think too much and just relax!
Angelia: ...Oh...
Angelia: Thanks, everybody...
Angelia: Sharice, you rarely vacation and yet you can't go home. I'm really sorry you have to accompany us.
Sharice: Queen, you mustn't say that. Actually, I don't want to go home. I'm actually more relaxed traveling with all of you.
Naya: We'll still need to give a hand to Sharice for being able to get this industrial vehicle. Not only could we hide inside, but we also could fit our luggage.
Sharice: That's...that's not it. It's just that I sent a letter to my family telling them that I was going to the lake with some friends for vacation.
Sharice: They insisted on having some workers hand over all this stuff in the vehicle to me...
Sione: Workers? Oh, yes. You're the daughter of the Carterwell merchants.
Naya: So all this strange stuff in the chariot was given to you by your family? Don't seem like Rune items to me. What is it?
Sharice: Hasn't summer been real hot recently?
Sharice: My parents think that waterside activities are an important future business opportunity. They made these toys for everybody to try out in the water.
Naya: Those are toys made just for the water!? Great. Well, let's get to Maple Lake and try them out!
Robber: This is a robbery! I'd advise you all to not make a move!
Sione: ...Time to do our work as bodyguards.
Naya: Ugh...please don't mention work.
Yan-Bo: Sharice has brought well-meaning women? Wah! Rare guests, indeed you are.
Sharice: Rat mon...
Sharice: Eh...Grandpa Yan-Bo, long time no see...
Yan-Bo: Very long indeed. Courteous, you must be. And these women are...?
Sharice: They're my friends. This is Sione, Naya, and...
Angelia: You can call me Angel. Grandpa Yan-Bo, hello.
Yan-Bo: You ladies come calling, is this for a particular reason?
Sharice: We came to pass the summer and enjoy the Maples. Oh, yeah! And we're going swimming!

Yan-Bo: Ah! Frolic in the water, you will? 
In me thou see'st the twilight of such day
As after sunset fadeth in the west...
Yan-Bo: Since this is so, in the depths of Maple Lake, a secret spot you should visit.
Yan-Bo: Tranquil and beautiful, this place is. Frogodiles, appear they will not. Perfect for you, I think.
Sharice: Maple Lake has a secret spot!?
Yan-Bo: If interested you are, I'll ask Hestia to take you there.
Naya: Wahhhh!!! What is this!!??
Angelia: Naya, what's wrong?
Naya: I wanted to help everyone with their luggage, then I saw that this bag had "Swimming Apparel" written on it.
Naya: So I opened it to take a look and...well, see for yourself!
Sione: This is what we're wearing!?
Angelia: Ummm, looks a little...skimpy...
